docs.lead_paragraph: The Cosmos said yesterday that the suspension of Johan Neeskens would continue through Sunday's Soccer Bowl and that Franz Beckenbauer's status was questionable. ''Johan Neeskens is not important to us right now,'' said Krikor Yepremian, general manager of the Cosmos and a member of the board of directors. ''The Soccer Bowl is our No. 1 priority. Maybe we'll take action on Johan after the Soccer Bowl.'' Neeskens was suspended Friday after he left the team without notice for the third time this season.
